CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 5, 1958, pg. B1, reads: " "Miss North Side" - in popularity contest sponsored by the Manchester Urban League, June 27, at Victory Baptist Church, Helen Fay Taylor was crowned "Miss North Side" by Betty Bostic. Left to right, front row: Maxine Heard, fourth place, and Murtle Melms, fifth place.  Second row: Ellen Nolan, second place; Miss Bostic, Miss Taylor and Patricia Gray, third place. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of popularity contest winners, from left, front row: Maxine Heard and Murtle Melms; second row: Ellen Nolan, Betty Bostic, crowning "Miss North Side" Helen Fay Taylor, and Patricia Gray, gathered in Victory Baptist Church
